title: BBC Music magazine - February 2014 [classical music]
description:
BBC Music magazine (February 2014)

ISSN: 0966-7180 | 110 pages | PDF


BBC Music Magazine is a must for anyone with a passion for classical music. Classical music connoisseurs and new enthusiast alike will enjoy the fascinating features and reviews of over 120 new works in every issue, including sections on jazz and world music.

In the February issue: Gustavo Dudamel talks to Richard Morrison; the inspirational French pianist Jean-Efflam Bavouzet shares his thoughts with interviewer James Naughtie; Paul Drive celebrates a remarkable composer, Sir Peter Maxwell Davies; and the voting begins for the 2014 BBC Music Magazine Awards.
